The Process In a large pot, sauté garlic and chili in extra virgin olive oil. Add broth and tomatoes. Add chicken. After about five minutes add potato. Cook on a gentle boil for about 15 minutes. Add beans, chard, carrots and celery, and simmer for a few more minutes. Don’t over cook. Ladle into warm bowls. Finish with parsley, Parmesan, and taste for salt and pepper.